1) Shorts Creator – Network18 Internship

Problem:
During this internship, I developed a tool called Shorts Creator because creating short video content from long videos manually 
can be time-consuming for content creators.

Approach:
The system automatically converts long YouTube videos into short clips. It first extracts audio from the video and 
performs speech-to-text transcription, then analyzes the text to identify important segments of the video and 
generates short clips from those parts.

Tools:
I implemented this system using Python, with FastAPI for the backend, HTML for the user interface, and 
the Gemini API for processing and analyzing the video content.

Impact:
This tool helps automate the creation of short-form content from long videos, making the process faster and
more efficient for content creators.

Follow up
2) How could you improve this system in the future?
The system could be improved by adding better segmentation, improved summarization techniques, and 
optimizing video processing for faster performance.

3) How do you ensure the generated shorts are correct?

Before finalizing the shorts, I implemented a validation step. The system presents the generated clips to the user so they 
can review them before final output. The user can accept, delete, or modify the segments, ensuring that the final shorts 
accurately represent the intended content.

4) What was the biggest challenge in this project?

One of the biggest challenges was the processing time required to generate the final short clips. 
When multiple clips need to be created from the video, generating them one by one can take more time. 
Since these clipping tasks are independent of each other, I applied parallel processing for the final shorts generation.
This allowed multiple clips to be created simultaneously, which significantly reduced the total processing time.

5) Why FastAPI used?

Flask → A lightweight Python framework used to build web applications and APIs.
FastAPI → A modern Python framework used to build high-performance APIs, especially useful for applications that need fast processing.

6) Remember of liberary used

yt-dlp → download video
AssemblyAI → transcript
Gemini API → analyze content
FFmpeg → create clips
FastAPI → backend
Jinja2 / HTML → interface

7) Why is this Shorts Creator project useful for a company when many AI tools already exist?

Although many AI tools exist, companies often need customized solutions that fit their specific workflow and content requirements. 
This project was useful because it provided a tailored system for automatically generating short clips from long videos, 
which can save time for content teams.

In media companies like Network18, a large amount of video content is produced daily. 
A tool like this helps quickly identify important segments and convert them into short-form content, 
which is very useful for platforms like YouTube Shorts or social media.

Additionally, building an internal solution allows the company to customize the processing pipeline, 
control the data, and integrate it with their existing systems, which may not always be possible with external tools.

